{
  "message": "fuzz(xattr-parsing): 20 structured seeds across namespaces \u00d7 value sizes\n\nfuzz_xattr_parsing drives parse_xattr_name \u2192 set_xattr \u2192 list_xattrs\n+ list_xattrs_for_access on a synthetic Ext4Inode + 4 KiB external\nblock. The harness's name-builder rotates through 9 shapes (user.X /\ntrusted.X / security.X / system.X / system.posix_acl_access /\nsystem.posix_acl_default / system.richacl / userX-no-dot / \"user.\")\nand validates that the visible-list (default reader) matches the\nadmin-list minus trusted entries. Existing 6 ad-hoc seeds covered\nonly a subset of namespaces and never the value-length boundary.\n\nAdds 20 seeds spanning every namespace \u00d7 every error path \u00d7 value\nboundaries:\n\n  Single-namespace happy paths:\n  * user. with simple value\n  * trusted. (visible only to admin readers)\n  * security. with realistic SELinux label payload\n  * system. with custom suffix\n  * literal system.posix_acl_access (4-byte payload)\n  * literal system.posix_acl_default\n  * literal system.richacl\n\n  Invalid-name parse-error paths:\n  * \"userX\" (no dot \u2014 namespace match fails)\n  * bare \"user.\" (empty suffix \u2014 namespace rejects)\n\n  Multi-entry shapes:\n  * 8 entries (MAX_ENTRIES) with mixed namespaces\n  * 3 all-trusted entries (drives the admin-only filter on every\n    iteration of list_xattrs)\n\n  Boundary lengths:\n  * value at MAX_VALUE_LEN reachable bound (255 bytes \u2014 `byte%257`\n    caps at 255)\n  * suffix at MAX_SUFFIX_LEN (48 bytes)\n  * empty value (zero-byte payload)\n  * long suffix + 200-byte value combined\n\n  Conflict / overwrite paths:\n  * duplicate name overwrite (same key, two values \u2014 second wins)\n  * same suffix in 4 different namespaces (user/trusted/security/\n    system) \u2014 namespace-distinct keying contract\n  * 8 trusted-namespace overwrites with 100-byte payloads\n    (drives the inline-to-external xattr spill path repeatedly)\n\n  Visibility mix:\n  * user.* + trusted.* + security.* + posix_acl_access +\n    system.richacl in one run \u2014 exercises both the visibility\n    filter and the literal-name branches\n  * three back-to-back literal-ACL writes\n\nValidated by an 11 s libFuzzer run: 65k executions over the new\ncorpus, no crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
